qas.question: Does the political party of Aung San Suu Ky hold any positions among the ruling faction ?
Are international monitors used in the elections of Burma ?

answers.text: The 2012 by-elections were also the first time that international representatives were allowed to monitor the voting process in Myanmar

qas.question: Who raised concerns of fraud in the elections held in the Burma 2012 elections ?

answers.text: the Freedom House organisation raised concerns

qas.question: Who was expelled from Myanmar before the elections of 2012 and what position did they hold ?

answers.text: Somsri Hananuntasuk, executive director of the Asian Network for Free Elections (ANFREL)

qas.question: Did all of the political prisoners obtain freedom due to the election in Burma of 2012 ?

answers.text: some other political prisoners have not been released

context: In 1 April 2012 by-elections the NLD won <a0_0>43 of the 45 available seats<a0_0/>; previously an illegal organisation, the NLD had never won a Burmese election until this time. <a1_0>The 2012 by-elections were also the first time that international representatives were allowed to monitor the voting process in Myanmar<a1_0/>. Following announcement of the by-elections, <a2_0>the Freedom House organisation raised concerns<a2_0/> about "reports of fraud and harassment in the lead up to elections, including the March 23 deportation of <a3_0>Somsri Hananuntasuk, executive director of the Asian Network for Free Elections (ANFREL)<a3_0/>, a regional network of civil society organisations promoting democratization." However, uncertainties exist as <a4_0>some other political prisoners have not been released<a4_0/> and clashes between Burmese troops and local insurgent groups continue.
